This paper is about cross-lingual word embeddings, which are widely used in natural language processing (NLP) and machine learning (ML) applications. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which covers NLP and related topics. The paper also discusses various optimization strategies and objective functions used in cross-lingual word embeddings, which are relevant to the sub-category cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper mentions evaluation methods and challenges, which are relevant to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval). Finally, the paper discusses the use of cross-lingual word embeddings in computer vision applications, which is relevant to cs.CV (Computer Vision).
